Directions: Base your answer to the following questions on the information below about two animals, the sea anemone and the clownfish, and on your knowledge of science.
Content: Clownfish are tiny, omnivorous fish that find shelter from predators in the poisonous tentacles of sea anemones. The sea anemones sting their prey to capture food, but the clownfish are not hurt by the stinging tentacles. The clownfish clean the tentacles of the sea anemone and scare off butterfly fish, which consume sea anemones.
